#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.h1:17-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\frames_troubleshooting.htm+html.body.h1:17-1"
msgid "Troubleshooting Frames"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:18-1
msgid ""
"Creating and configuring frames to do what you want is a series of fairly "
"simple steps, but there are quite a few steps, and frames can do a lot. Some "
"of the time, frames will not work, or they might not work the way you "
"expect. This topic addresses several situations you might encounter when "
"working with frames, and provides some tips for correcting the situation."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:19-1
msgid "Tips are provided for the following situations:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:21-1
msgid "When a frame is inactive where you want to use it"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:22-1
msgid "When a frame is active where you do not want to use it"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:23-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\frames_troubleshooting.htm+html.body.ul.li:23-1"
msgid "When a frame does not perform the actions you set for it"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:24-1
msgid "When a frame performs actions more frequently than you expect"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:25-1
msgid "When information sent to a Braille display is not properly updated"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:26-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\frames_troubleshooting.htm+html.body.ul.li:26-1"
msgid "When Braille Information is not Displayed"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:28-1
msgid "When a Frame is Inactive Where you Want to Use it"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:29-1
msgid ""
"If your frame is inactive when you expected it to be available, or when you "
"open Frame Viewer, first make sure you opened Frame Viewer from the location "
"at which the frame was created. All frames are application specific. You "
"cannot create frames in one application and use them in another."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:30-1
msgid ""
"If you open Frame Viewer and your frames are inactive, you cannot move to "
"them."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:32-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">TAB</b> to the Frames List button and press "
"<b>SPACEBAR</b>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.ol.li:33-1
msgid ""
"Move to the frame you wish to work with, and press <b>ALT+P</b> to open the "
"frame's properties."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:35-1
msgid ""
"When you first create a frame, two Validation Rules are set. A rule is set "
"for the window title to contain the text it did at the time the frame was "
"created. A rule is also set for the window class to contain the text it did "
"at the time the frame was created. Verify this information has not changed "
"in the application, or turn off one of the rules. In the Validation Rules "
"page of frame properties, select a rule in the list and press <b>SPACEBAR</"
"b> to toggle it off or back on again."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:36-1
msgid ""
"Add another comparison value. The rule will be valid if one or the other of "
"the values match the information in the application."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:37-1
msgid ""
"Change the comparison type to something less specific, for example, from Is "
"to Contains. Shorten the comparison value so it only contains text that does "
"not change."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:38-1
msgid "When a Frame is Active Where you do not Want to Use it"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:39-1
msgid ""
"If your frame is active in places where you do not want it speaking "
"information or performing other actions, your validation rules are too "
"general. Look at the window title (<b>INSERT+T</b>), window class "
"(<strong>CTRL+INSERT+F1</strong>), or text within the area (or areas) where "
"you wish to use the frame. Look for something unique to that area or those "
"areas. Set up a validation rule for that unique information."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:40-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\frames_troubleshooting.htm+html.body.h2:40-1"
msgid "When a frame does not perform the actions you set for it"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:41-1
msgid ""
"All frame actions are based on events. Make sure the event is occurring as "
"you expect. There are only three events that directly cause actions to take "
"place: focus moving into the area of the frame (On Focus), new text (of some "
"type) being newly displayed within the area of the frame (On Text), or "
"pressing an assigned keystroke (On Frame Key). The fourth event type (On "
"Play Action) lets you set an action in one frame to occur when one of the "
"other events takes place in another frame."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:42-1
msgid ""
"Create events to try and verify when events are occurring. Create an On "
"Focus event with the action, Say String. Have it state, \"Focus Event.\" Try "
"a similar test with the On Text event. Try assigning the action to the On "
"Frame Key event, assign a keystroke, and test it."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:43-1
msgid "When a Frame Performs Actions More Frequently than you Expect"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:44-1
msgid ""
"Not all actions take place because of the frame events you have set. Some "
"actions are caused by system events and the JAWS script support. Most "
"frequently, these actions are initiated by FocusChangeEvent, or "
"NewTextEvent. To test to see if this is the cause of the situation, create "
"an On Focus event in your frame with the action set to Suppress Script "
"Event. If this does not resolve the situation, create an On Text event with "
"the action set to Suppress Script Event."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:45-1
msgid ""
"The On Text event, when set to filter for any highlighted text, will perform "
"the associated action each time the text that is highlighted changes - for "
"example, when moving through a list box. Try changing the scope of the event "
"to only when focus is in the frame, or to only when focus is not within the "
"frame."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:46-1
msgid "When Information Sent to a Braille Display is not Properly Updated"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:47-1
msgid ""
"When you use any of the Braille related actions to send information to a "
"Braille display, the display may not properly refresh when you move focus to "
"another control or perform other actions in your application. To prevent "
"this, ensure the Show Focus Control check box is checked. This check box is "
"located in the Add/Modify Event dialogs, on the page that is displayed after "
"one of the Braille actions is assigned."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:48-1
msgctxt "HTM_po_nelkul\\frames_troubleshooting.htm+html.body.h2:48-1"
msgid "When Braille Information is not Displayed"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5Cframes_troubleshooting.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:49-1
msgid ""
"If you configure a frame to send information to a Braille display, but the "
"information is not displayed, verify that you are using structured mode. The "
"frame actions related to Braille do not work while you are using line mode "
"as line mode is an actual representation of what is displayed on the screen. "
"While using structured mode, you can set your frames to send the information "
"you find useful to your Braille display."
msgstr ""

